David Marshall was on licence for sexually assaulting a 14-year-old girl when he killed Eni Mevish . 
  He stabbed her in the heart, lungs and liver six months after they met . 
  Marshall must serve a minimum of 20 years for the murder of the student . 
  The pair met on a canal towpath while she was out jogging . 
  He was 'jealous' of her friendships and stabbed her with a kitchen knife at her home in Stoke-on-Trent . 
  Marshall was jailed for 20 years and six months at Stafford Crown Court . 
 